  ### Missed Topic 1: Sequence with a logical expression

  Up until now, our sequences have mostly looked at one signal at a time (like  req == 1 ). But what if a rule requires two signals to be
  checked on the exact same clock cycle?

  • What is it? It is using boolean logic (like  &&  or  || ) inside a sequence.
  • The Rule: Both signals must be checked at the exact same moment.

  Syntax:

    sequence seq_logical;
      (req && enable); // Both must be 1 on the exact same clock edge!
    endsequence

  If  req  is 1, but  enable  is 0, this sequence will fail instantly.
