  ### Missed Topic 3: Timing Windows ( ##[min:max] )

  So far, we have only used Fixed Delays (like  ##3 ). If we write  ##3 ack , the assertion demands that the  ack  arrives on the exact 3rd
  clock cycle. If it arrives on cycle 2 or cycle 4, it fails!

  But in the real world, hardware is sometimes unpredictable. A memory chip might take anywhere from 1 to 3 clock cycles to reply. If we use
  ##3 , the assertion will falsely fail if the memory replies quickly on cycle 1!

  To fix this, we use a Timing Window (a range of time).

  Your syllabus defines 3 specific types of Timing Windows:

  #### 1. Standard Timing Window ( ##[1:3] )

  • What it means: The signal can arrive on clock cycle 1, OR cycle 2, OR cycle 3.
  • Syntax:

    property p_window;
      @(posedge clk) (req == 1) |-> ##[1:3] (ack == 1);
    endproperty

  • Inch-by-Inch: When  req  is 1, a timer starts. If  ack  is 1 on the next clock, it PASSES. If not, it waits. If  ack  is 1 on the 2nd
  clock, it PASSES. If not, it waits. If  ack  is 1 on the 3rd clock, it PASSES. If  ack  is still 0 after the 3rd clock, it finally FAILS.

  #### 2. Overlapping Timing Window ( ##[0:3] )

  • What it means: The zero ( 0 ) means the signal is allowed to happen on the exact same clock cycle that the request was made, OR any time
  up to cycle 3.
  • Syntax:

    property p_overlap_window;
      @(posedge clk) (req == 1) |-> ##[0:3] (ack == 1);
    endproperty

  • Inch-by-Inch: When  req  is 1, it checks  ack  immediately on that exact same clock edge ( ##0 ). If  ack  is 1, it PASSES instantly. If
  not, it keeps checking on cycle 1, 2, and 3.

  #### 3. Indefinite Timing Window ( ##[1:$] )

  • What it means: The  $  symbol means Infinity (End of simulation). It is called the "eventuality" operator.
  • Syntax:

    property p_indefinite;
      @(posedge clk) (req == 1) |-> ##[1:$] (ack == 1);
    endproperty

  • Inch-by-Inch: When  req  is 1, it waits for  ack  to become 1. It will wait forever. It will check cycle 1, cycle 2, cycle 100, cycle 10,
  000. It will never throw a FAIL unless the entire simulation ends ( $finish ) and  ack  never arrived!
  ──────
  Summary:

  •  ##3  = Must happen exactly on 3.
  •  ##[1:3]  = Can happen on 1, 2, or 3.
  •  ##[0:3]  = Can happen right now (0), 1, 2, or 3.
  •  ##[1:$]  = Can happen anytime between now and the end of the universe!


